        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 9:17PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 917 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Four Way, or 10 miles southwest of Dumas, moving
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Masterson, Four Way, and Lake Meredith.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
